This paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval, which are both sub-fields of computer science. The use of Google search and webpages to extract meaning from words suggests that this paper belongs to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves probability and similarity distance functions, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of webpages and search engines also suggests that this paper could belong to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of data and the development of algorithms, which are topics commonly studied in data science (cs.DS).
